h3. Summary
From time to time, Jira's *{{fieldlayoutschemeentity}}* table has abandoned references from a field configuration to a field configuration scheme. 

h3. Steps to Reproduce
Apart from manually deleting field configuration schemes from the database, it's not clear how this issue can be reproduced. 

h3. Expected Results
The integrity checker should remove missing references. 

h3. Actual Results
The integrity checker should remove missing references from the *{{fieldlayoutschemeentity}}* table. 
The following error is logged:
{noformat}
com.atlassian.cache.CacheException: com.atlassian.jira.exception.DataAccessException: No FieldLayoutScheme found for id 22601
{noformat}

h3.Workaround
{panel:borderColor=#FFE7E7|bgColor=#FFE7E7}
(i) *{{DELETE}}* statements are to be used at your own risk and aren't supported by Atlassian.
(i) Take a database dump before deleting rows from your database. 
{panel}
Delete the missing references: 
{code:sql|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#6A8EB3|bgColor=#F8F8F8}
DELETE FROM fieldlayoutschemeentity WHERE scheme NOT IN (SELECT id FROM fieldlayoutscheme);
{code}

h3. Issue Summary

While developing a JIRA Server (7.7.1) P2 Plugin, I have discovered that updating an entity property via the [Issue Edit REST endpoint|https://docs.atlassian.com/software/jira/docs/api/REST/7.6.6/#api/2/issue-editIssue] results in no IssuePropertySetEvent being published.
h3. Environment
 * JIRA Server 7.7.1

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a P2 Plugin with an EventListener for the IssuePropertySetEvent
{code:java}
@Component
public class MyEventListener implements InitializingBean, DisposableBean {
    private static Logger log = LoggerFactory.getLogger(MyEventListener.class);

    private final EventPublisher eventPublisher;

    @Inject
    public StreamHubEventListener(@ComponentImport final EventPublisher eventPublisher) {
        this.eventPublisher = eventPublisher;
    }

 /**
     * Starts generating issueEvents after plugin becomes enabled such as on plugin redeploy or on system startup.
     */
    @Override
    public void afterPropertiesSet() {
        eventPublisher.register(this);
    }

    /**
     * Stops generating streamhub issueEvents whenever the plugin is disabled or the system is shut down.
     */
    @Override
    public void destroy() {
        eventPublisher.unregister(this);
    }

    @EventListener
     public void onIssueEntityPropertySet(final IssuePropertySetEvent entityPropertySetEvent) {
           log.info("Event received");       
     }
{code}
 # Start up a local Jira with the plugin {code}atlas-debug{code}
 # Create an issue, e.g. HSP-1
 # Perform a PUT to
{code:java}
http://localhost:2990/jira/rest/api/2/issue/HSP-1{code}
with contents:
{code:java}
{
  "update": {
    "summary": [
      {
        "set": "My new summary"
      }
    ]
  },
  "properties": [
    {
      "key": "key1",
      "value": "{\"key\":\"value\"}"
    }
  ]
}
{code}

h3. Expected Results

The EventListener should be triggered with the change to the issue's entity property.
h3. Actual Results

No event is being published and therefore cannot be listened to.
h3. Workaround

Only perform updates to the issue entity properties via the [Set Issue Property REST Endpoint|https://docs.atlassian.com/software/jira/docs/api/REST/7.6.6/#api/2/issue/\{issueIdOrKey\}/properties-setProperty]. Otherwise there is no workaround.
